ive pointer years during the last decades suggests that increasing climatic variability together with rising temperatures might be influencing growth of Fagus at the more humid sites. If we substitute space by time it seems that already small changes in precipitation regime can have considerable impact, especially on the growth of beech. Other, more drought tolerant species like oak might gain competitive advantages under the projected climatic changes. © 2011 Elsevier B.V.},
   author = {Tobias Scharnweber and Michael Manthey and Christian Criegee and Andreas Bauwe and Christian Schröder and Martin Wilmking},
